        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection consists chiefly of correspondence, memoranda, pamphlets, leaflets, newsletters and anniversary publications distributed by the Veterans of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade (VALB) from the 1940s through 1983. Also contains material related to, aid to Spanish refuges, including publications and reports from the Joint Anti-Fascist Refugee Committee, and a photocopy of Harris' questionnaire from John Dollard's Yale University study "Fear and Courage under Battle Conditions.</p>
